e\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"summary_text\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"**Considering coverage maps**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI’m pondering whether native agent coverage maps only test with direct usage. It seems like this could limit the scope of what we learn from those tests. I wonder if they’re capturing enough real-world scenarios or if they’re missing out on potential issues. It's something worth thinking about more, as I really want to ensure that these maps are providing valuable insights for users. Let's explore this further.\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"summary_text\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"**Considering Java list methods**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI’m thinking about how commonly `java/util/LinkedList` and `java/util/ArrayList` are used in reverse. They return an `AbstractList`, which is interesting. I also need to figure out if the `classWriter` should use `COMPUTE_FRAMES` only and not `COMPUTE_MAXS`, but the docs say it implies both. Maybe it’s safer to use `COMPUTE_FRAMES | COMPUTE_MAXS` just in case? I want to stay dynamic in my approach while figuring this out!\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"}, {\\\"type\\\": \\\"toolCall\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"call_Dzyg7e48PEax6gOr1npXYmQg|fc_0237394f573391680169fb8e2362b881a0ac261eafdde88075\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"write\\\", \\\"arguments\\\": {\\\"path\\\": \\\"tests/src/asm/asm/3.1/src/test/java/asm/asm/ClassWriterTest.java\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"/*\\\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\\\n *\\\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\\\n */\\\\npackage asm.asm;\\\\n\\\\nimport java.util.AbstractList;\\\\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\\\\nimport java.util.LinkedList;\\\\nimport java.util.List;\\\\n\\\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\\\nimport org.objectweb.asm.ClassReader;\\\\nimport org.objectweb.asm.ClassWriter;\\\\nimport org.objectweb.asm.Label;\\\\nimport org.objectweb.asm.MethodVisitor;\\\\n\\\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\\\nimport static org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes.ACC_PUBLIC;\\\\nimport static org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes.ACC_STATIC;\\\\nimport static org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes.ACC_SUPER;\\\\nimport static org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes.ALOAD;\\\\nimport static org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes.ARETURN;\\\\nimport static org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes.ASTORE;\\\\nimport static org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes.DUP;\\\\nimport static org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes.GOTO;\\\\nimport static org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes.IFEQ;\\\\nimport static org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes.ILOAD;\\\\nimport static org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes.INVOKESPECIAL;\\\\nimport static org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes.NEW;\\\\nimport static org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes.RETURN;\\\\nimport static org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes.V1_6;\\\\n\\\\npublic class ClassWriterTest {\\\\n    private static final String GENERATED_CLASS = \\\\\\\"asm/asm/GeneratedCollectionSelector\\\\\\\";\\\\n\\\\n    @Test\\\\n    void computesCommonSuperClassWhenStackMapFramesMergeDifferentBranches() {\\\\n        RecordingClassWriter classWriter = new RecordingClassWriter();\\\\n        classWriter.visit(V1_6, ACC_PUBLIC + ACC_SUPER, GENERATED_CLASS, null, \\\\\\\"java/lang/Object\\\\\\\", null);\\\\n        writeDefaultConstructor(classWriter);\\\\n        writeCollectionSelectorMethod(classWriter);\\\\n        classWriter.visitEnd();\\\\n\\\\n        byte[] classBytes = classWriter.toByteArray();\\\\n\\\\n        assertThat(new ClassReader(classBytes).getClassName()).isEqualTo(GENERATED_CLASS);\\\\n        assertThat(classWriter.commonSuperClasses()).contains(internalName(AbstractList.class));\\\\n    }\\\\n\\\\n    private static void writeDefaultConstructor(final ClassWriter classWriter) {\\\\n        MethodVisitor methodVisitor = classWriter.visitMethod(ACC_PUBLIC, \\\\\\\"<init>\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"()V\\\\\\\", null, null);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitCode();\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitVarInsn(ALOAD, 0);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitMethodInsn(INVOKESPECIAL, \\\\\\\"java/lang/Object\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"<init>\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"()V\\\\\\\");\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitInsn(RETURN);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitMaxs(0, 0);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitEnd();\\\\n    }\\\\n\\\\n    private static void writeCollectionSelectorMethod(final ClassWriter classWriter) {\\\\n        MethodVisitor methodVisitor = classWriter.visitMethod(\\\\n                ACC_PUBLIC + ACC_STATIC,\\\\n                \\\\\\\"choose\\\\\\\",\\\\n                \\\\\\\"(Z)Ljava/lang/Object;\\\\\\\",\\\\n                null,\\\\n                null);\\\\n        Label linkedListBranch = new Label();\\\\n        Label returnValue = new Label();\\\\n\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitCode();\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitVarInsn(ILOAD, 0);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitJumpInsn(IFEQ, linkedListBranch);\\\\n        writeNewInstance(methodVisitor, ArrayList.class);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitVarInsn(ASTORE, 1);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitJumpInsn(GOTO, returnValue);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitLabel(linkedListBranch);\\\\n        writeNewInstance(methodVisitor, LinkedList.class);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitVarInsn(ASTORE, 1);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitLabel(returnValue);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitVarInsn(ALOAD, 1);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitInsn(ARETURN);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitMaxs(0, 0);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitEnd();\\\\n    }\\\\n\\\\n    private static void writeNewInstance(final MethodVisitor methodVisitor, final Class<?> type) {\\\\n        String internalName = internalName(type);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitTypeInsn(NEW, internalName);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitInsn(DUP);\\\\n        methodVisitor.visitMethodInsn(INVOKESPECIAL, internalName, \\\\\\\"<init>\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"()V\\\\\\\");\\\\n    }\\\\n\\\\n    private static String internalName(final Class<?> type) {\\\\n        return type.getName().replace('.', '/');\\\\n    }\\\\n\\\\n    private static final class RecordingClassWriter extends ClassWriter {\\\\n        private final List<String> commonSuperClasses = new ArrayList<String>();\\\\n\\\\n        private RecordingClassWriter() {\\\\n            super(ClassWriter.COMPUTE_FRAMES | ClassWriter.COMPUTE_MAXS);\\\\n        }\\\\n\\\\n        @Override\\\\n        protected String getCommonSuperClass(final String type1, final String type2) {\\\\n            String commonSuperClass = super.getCommonSuperClass(type1, type2);\\\\n            commonSuperClasses.add(commonSuperClass);\\\\n            return commonSuperClass;\\\\n        }\\\\n\\\\n        private List<String> commonSuperClasses() {\\\\n            return commonSuperClasses;\\\\n        }\\\\n    }\\\\n}\\\\n\\\"}}], \\\"api\\\": \\\"openai-responses\\\", \\\"provider\\\": \\\"OCA\\\", \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.5\\\", \\\"usage\\\": {\\\"input\\\": 392, \\\"output\\\": 2856, \\\"cacheRead\\\": 28672, \\\"cacheWrite\\\": 0, \\\"totalTokens\\\": 31920, \\\"cost\\\": {\\\"input\\\": 0, \\\"output\\\": 0, \\\"cacheRead\\\": 0, \\\"cacheWrite\\\": 0, \\\"total\\\": 0}}, \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"toolUse\\\", \\\"timestamp\\\": 1778093580834, \\\"responseId\\\": \\\"resp_0237394f573391680169fb8e0dc76c81a0949e17ec3e52a8fb\\\"}}\\n2232:[tool-exec] end id=call_Dzyg7e48PEax6gOr1npXYmQg|fc_0237394f573391680169fb8e2362b881a0ac261eafdde88075 name=write status=success\\n2236:[recv] {\\\"type\\\": \\\"turn_end\\\", \\\"message\\\": {\\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\", \\\"content\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"thinking\\\", \\\"thinking\\\": \\\"**Considering coverage maps**\\\\n\\\\nI’m pondering whether native agent coverage maps only test with direct usage. It seems like this could limit the scope of what we learn from those tests. I wonder if they’re capturing enough real-world scenarios or if they’re missing out on potential issues. It's something worth thinking about more, as I really want to ensure that these maps are providing valuable insights for users. Let's explore this further.\\\\n\\\\n**Considering Java list methods**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about how commonly `java/util/LinkedList` and `java/util/ArrayList` are used in reverse. They return an `AbstractList`, which is interesting. I also need to figure out if the `classWriter` should use `COMPUTE_FRAMES` only and not `COMPUTE_MAXS`, but the docs say it implies both. Maybe it’s safer to use `COMPUTE_FRAMES | COMPUTE_MAXS` just in case? I want to stay dynamic in my approach while figuring this out!\\\", \\\"thinkingSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"rs_0237394f573391680169fb8e0e6bf881a0b0dabfff57628dc3\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"reasoning\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"encrypted_content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"gAAAAABp-44jUwyu7yBpuOclad0VwgoiFWjOJvJL6YZhj4uUV5pNqvlb939lvSxdLQ-tlq-l6L8yy5La7IK-6-SWz1w-yMgrQGRfZ1sYNUFd5mDPoNN6KxmNfrNdbz_fagzfAQTtTMYqe17FwCy_BeUKnNkmTshyV7n9rn9zJkRYUz7mm4kfnp1A4mjzlCW-ZQ5S1KMkZfza0yTB8d9a7eKAUz1vSpOwVNrRmcF9GKQ7GoeYnaiN125zvzwHPtkmxu5iHX3B1ujHi00yLti7LpP4VZJwQvVGDaffAMHg9WUPDndZw94LtBoxCaM7FfYkjJ_86sW_YAMk4qz0qJOdNpe9_nST-or1Op0a6fhUTOuUYHc404X2ZGXbLqRmZbSjb35W2Mk_JeD49S-On1mlPhR13Cf5wGg7BUqxYqp0oZSWOC8PpWZpBaWze_vhZgFr0i_6Hcpj3W4Up6SS1ws63TenQAHUT712GT4hvAVp02eK00pSZUo179tSYMn4VnX2tysSQi8LYmfHTb-tyZv4v2Szc8HrzNypm-Ff_HI0GZ4Jc_wBAxhtKM2_xbVK0nlaLMkPVH4BNKcyuc8AeEx_ugKYep_z0v1BTZ1HpxAdZQ4l9OBGwZ3Phy-j-mSpaQrs4rwEoWCmEiO3EPmpqKzsx43hjc7SY2GfAFRG4wJOuyoactHAA1DavGIIAJXIxDQ_ctNDH5npZcezFiCMw1VhKJ9W3rjQas4ft-RxWoewL5bcV7OJbg3E0o0EUQC8eaAsmNpwb8fOTajQ7DyI84rUfKzw5Plt37yi6PE9uQZe93FEQRxE4pJTt86iNBp43CJ_KCRFsTnasQoPlVYb5CTmH66WcUo6GiaLO5p4YNlDW7qw9bXXG8glTXTNKxJ_hzvcwsDJ4qByijJNyYamEgAoypsd1YxVjYwV8xtG0WoGO3X6LkrX27LXa0JpnuFtbm9dIy41cpaa4KxupLoQPsRjyO11BZRLZiOA4Z_sAgsPDpfWX8GuLdAZAYsSoSAMr4pjIRwv8x_UZHpp919gqvlSmXMeKNWM8yxsG6wOk5iFT1iM_9DYOH2pfvdHxSjXNfpqDlO7HitPueh_YMhZ_qG9MsL7tu8d_ZejvcoYAN4wNjfvJSUq5vCBPZ53n8064_D3BRT4a2LI9KSExcpBgDQ89d5n1iXSN3b4hMlV235mJHETcCRdwInOMzisjrZcKkgJnkQZ4bkDiSWQ3nVOJ10MH7qBy9njJsgHfVU9qqQn5vIBTyQ7m-bHUJNsqqdaCCLm-i9fZBDQrbNpupY